C \in \mathbb{R}
y^{\prime}+xy=C
\int Ce^{\frac{x^2}{2}}dx
e^{\frac{x^2}2}y=C\int e^{\frac{x^2}2}dx
y=Ce^{-\frac{x^2}2}\int e^{\frac{x^2}2}dx
\frac{d}{dx}(e^{\frac{x^2}{2}}y) = e^{\frac{x^2}{2}}(\frac{dy}{dx}+xy) = C e^{\frac{x^2}{2}}
e^{\frac{x^2}{2}}y(x) - y(0) = C \int_0^x e^{\frac{t^2}{2}} dt
y(x) = e^{-\frac{x^2}{2}}y(0)+C\int_0^x e^{\frac{t^2-x^2}{2}} dt
